Bureau of Engraving and Printing portrait of Crawford as Secretary of the Treasury


William Harris Crawford (February 24, 1772 – September 15, 1834) was an American politician and judge during the early 19th century. He served as United States Secretary of War from 1815 to 1816 and United States Secretary of the Treasury from 1816 to 1825. He also ran for President in the 1824 election.



